<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: MERITOR WABCO WITH "D" VERSION ECU - TROUBLESHOOTING - VALVE TESTS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="2">
        <title>VALVE TESTS</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x0403702">
            <title>ABS Modulator Valve</title>
            <para>Measure resistance across each valve solenoid coil terminal and ground on the ABS valve to ensure 4.0
                to 8.0 ohms for a 12-volt system (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0403720">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0403720" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0403720.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. ABS Valve Solenoid Coil Terminals and Ground</caption>
            </figure>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If the resistance is greater than 8.0 ohms for a 12-volt system, clean the electrical contacts
                        in the solenoid. Check the resistance again.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To check the cable and the ABS valves as one unit, measure resistance across the pins on the
                        ECU connector of the harness. (See
                        <hotlnk document="s04037_16.xml" xrefid="x0403707">Appendix II, Wiring Diagrams</hotlnk>.)
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0403708">
            <title>ATC Valve</title>
            <para>Measure resistance across the two electrical terminals on the ATC valve to ensure 8.0 to 14.0 ohms for
                a 12-volt system (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0403721">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0403721" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0403721.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. ATC Valve Electrical Terminals</caption>
            </figure>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If the resistance is greater than 14.0 ohms for a 12-volt system, clean the electrical
                        contacts on the solenoid. Check the resistance again.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>o check the cable and ATC valve as one unit, measure resistance across the pins on the ECU
                        connector of the harness. (See
                        <hotlnk document="s04037_16.xml" xrefid="x0403707">Appendix II, Wiring Diagrams</hotlnk>.)
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>See
                        <hotlnk document="s04037_17.xml" xrefid="x0403711">Appendix III</hotlnk>
                        for ABS Valve Package Troubleshooting Guide.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
